Very powerful and compelling arguments that as a Jewish person reading this, I'd be like, okay, but then you start picking up all these different stories of the people in between.

22:41.040 --> 22:42.822
And you're like, this doesn't make sense.

22:43.643 --> 22:49.010
How could the savior of the world come through this genealogy?

22:50.530 --> 22:53.413
We see that this family line is far from perfect, perfect.

22:53.433 --> 23:02.782
There are faithful people in this lineage of Jesus, and there are also people who may struggle to even reconcile as worth following, i.e.

23:02.862 --> 23:03.462
King David.

23:03.823 --> 23:07.106
Quite honestly, I struggle to read sometimes the words of King David.

23:07.126 --> 23:10.169
I'm like, man, this guy, he kind of messed up a lot.

23:11.991 --> 23:17.416
And yet Jesus is portrayed as the climax of this bloodline.

23:18.397 --> 23:19.698
He is perfection.

23:20.994 --> 23:27.423
God made into man, stepped into his own creation, coming through a family tree that is marred by sin and shame.

23:27.483 --> 23:34.553
Through this imperfect family tree, we see that God is indeed good on making due his promise.

23:35.535 --> 23:42.505
We say that with promises, you either make the promise and you fulfill them, or they remain unfulfilled.

23:43.426 --> 23:48.914
And you see that the faithfulness of God leads him to actually fulfill the promises

23:49.058 --> 23:52.482
that he would make, that he made in the Old Testament.

23:53.684 --> 24:09.785
Through this imperfect family tree, God shows that no amount of sin could thwart the birth of Jesus Christ, who would ultimately live the perfect life that we could not live, died that the only he could die, and resurrect from the grave, the only act that he could do.

24:09.825 --> 24:17.234
We see that sin truly did not have any ability

24:17.826 --> 24:28.037
to stop God's plan of redemption for the world, not through the family lineage, nor could sin keep Jesus in that grave.

24:29.879 --> 24:35.305
Because as we know, Jesus resurrects from the grave three days later, conquering sin, Satan, and death.

24:37.687 --> 24:43.734
The promise of God stands firm in the life, death, burial, and resurrection of Jesus.

24:45.075 --> 24:47.698
But this promise is not just an ethereal promise,

24:48.194 --> 24:50.117
Okay.

24:50.137 --> 24:54.803
This promise is not just some ethereal promise that we're like, oh, that sounds great.

24:55.244 --> 24:56.366
Let's move on with our lives.

24:57.427 --> 25:01.873
It is a promise that we can have hope and a promise that we can find assurance in.

25:02.234 --> 25:06.019
I probably read this quote to you guys multiple times.

25:06.500 --> 25:08.683
I'm sorry if it's getting old.

25:09.184 --> 25:10.345
I love this quote.

25:10.405 --> 25:11.587
It's from Dr. Tim Keller.

25:12.709 --> 25:13.290
Rest in peace.

25:13.310 --> 25:14.031
This is what he says.

25:15.092 --> 25:16.434
He says Aristotle.

25:16.706 --> 25:23.994
thought it was impossible that humans could be friend with a God, because friends have things in common, and can say, oh, you too?

25:25.096 --> 25:32.904
But in becoming human, God's first great act of friendship, he became like us, drawing near to us so we could draw near to him.

25:33.545 --> 25:34.266
Let me read that line.

25:34.406 --> 25:41.094
He became like us, drawing near to us so that we could draw near to him, since he humbled himself to get near us.

25:41.434 --> 25:44.978
Only the humble, not the hottie, can be his friends.

25:46.114 --> 25:49.678
In his second great act of friendship, he gave his life for us.

25:50.479 --> 25:54.363
In our suffering then, we can look at Jesus and say, you too.

25:55.785 --> 26:04.435
Dr. Tim Keller, he says this quote in the context of what is needed in building a relationship with someone.

26:05.456 --> 26:09.841
It is that moment that when you find someone in your life and you say, oh, you too?

26:10.802 --> 26:12.724
Oh, you like anime too?

26:13.265 --> 26:14.066
Oh, me too.

26:14.722 --> 26:18.067
Oh, your family is also messed up, mine too.

26:20.229 --> 26:24.635
It's in this context of oh, you too, you as well.

26:26.518 --> 26:29.922
Oh, your family history, Jesus is not perfect.

26:30.503 --> 26:34.328
Oh, you come from a broken family with messed up people.

26:34.969 --> 26:39.876
Oh, you, you Jesus also suffered while living on this earth.

26:40.637 --> 26:41.458
Oh, you too.

26:43.266 --> 26:44.928
God became like us.

26:46.650 --> 26:59.046
He came in ultimate humility, born in a manger, born to an embarrassing family situation, born from a lineage of people who are faulty and sin-ridden members of God's chosen people.

26:59.947 --> 27:04.913
And in this case, we can relate to Jesus, and he can relate to us.

27:06.695 --> 27:12.402
Jesus was, in fact, the son of God, full in his deity, but he was also known as the son of man.

27:12.642 --> 27:13.964
full in his humanity.

27:16.587 --> 27:26.461
Though he is very much 100% God, he too is 100% man, and Jesus' life shows that he can in fact relate with us.

27:27.983 --> 27:36.355
Though Jesus was and is perfect, he is without sin, he invites us into his messy family.

27:39.359 --> 27:41.842
We'll close with a passage from the Book of Romans,

27:42.786 --> 27:44.809
Romans 8, verse 15 through 17.

27:45.750 --> 27:46.832
The Apostle Paul writes this.

27:49.896 --> 27:50.096
Excuse me.

27:50.116 --> 27:53.161
For you did not receive a spirit of slavery to fall back into fear.

27:53.862 --> 27:59.470
Instead, you received the spirit of adoption by whom we cry out, Abba Father.

28:00.912 --> 28:10.866
The spirit himself testifies together with our spirit that we are God's children and if children also heirs, heirs of God and co-heirs with Christ.

28:11.330 --> 28:24.588
because if we indeed suffer with Him, so that we may also be glorified with Him, we have received a spirit of adoption by whom we cry our Abba Father.

28:27.131 --> 28:37.906
God's promise to us is not about, and please hear this, His promise to us, if you read throughout the scripture, is not about a wealthier life,

28:38.498 --> 28:41.442
God's promise to us is not about a healthier life.

28:42.404 --> 28:45.829
God's promise to us is not about a more relaxed life.

28:47.331 --> 28:51.177
God's promise to us is not even about a life without suffering.

28:51.217 --> 28:54.401
God's promise to us today.

28:54.461 --> 29:03.154
His commitment to us is that if you accept Jesus' invitation to a life with him, there is a seed at the table for you.

29:04.898 --> 29:06.780
There is room for us in God's kingdom.

29:06.800 --> 29:14.290
There's a relationship forged between us and God and we get to call him Father and he calls us his children.

29:15.191 --> 29:22.801
God's promise to us is that we get to be heirs of God and co-heirs with our big brother Jesus and the inheritance.

29:23.943 --> 29:25.204
It's not a better life.

29:25.765 --> 29:27.227
It's not a life without suffering.

29:27.547 --> 29:32.754
It's not a wealthier life or whatever, but it is eternal life.

29:33.666 --> 29:39.956
eternal life that is promising to hear in now and after we die.

29:41.418 --> 29:48.069
God's promise to us is given through an invitation to enter into a redeemed family.

29:49.451 --> 29:52.556
It's crazy because I don't know what your life looks like right now.

29:52.576 --> 29:58.866
I don't know whether or not you have accepted this invitation by God, but if you have not

29:59.266 --> 30:00.167
Consider it today.

30:00.247 --> 30:03.751
Consider being invited into this redeemed family.

30:03.771 --> 30:08.516
I don't know if you've ever been invited to your friends, your friends, families, Thanksgiving dinner, right?

30:08.877 --> 30:10.719
It's kind of like that, but better, all right?

30:11.720 --> 30:23.714
The invitation of God, the promise of God is an invitation to join this redeemed family called the church or the body of Christ, which admittedly may be messier times.

30:23.894 --> 30:27.538
And again, probably doesn't have the best street cred right now in our cultural moment.

30:28.898 --> 30:34.769
But Jesus' invitation to us is to join this redeemed family.

30:37.013 --> 30:43.244
But as we saw in Jesus' own family tree, he doesn't necessarily come from the best line of people.

30:45.067 --> 30:50.056
In a sense, he's kind of sandwiched between really like messy people and then you have Jesus.

30:50.738 --> 30:53.202
And then everyone else after that, meaning us,

30:53.570 --> 30:56.113
It's not really like, it's not the best, right?

30:56.253 --> 31:04.862
He sandwiched in between very imperfect sections of a family that tries to understand what it means to be God's people.

31:06.243 --> 31:13.411
One family tree that pointed to his arrival and one part of the family tree that points back to the person that we're trying to become.

31:15.613 --> 31:20.658
Our Lord and Savior, the Messiah, our big brother, our friend, our King, Jesus Christ.

31:22.274 --> 31:28.810
Jesus' invitation is to join this redeemed family that is trying to become more and more like him.

31:30.234 --> 31:38.514
Through his messy lineage, Jesus arrives on the scene and proves God's faithfulness to the world, that no amount of sinful people

31:39.202 --> 31:40.925
could thwart his arrival on earth.

31:41.225 --> 31:50.420
Then no amount of sin could thwart his promise to rescue the world from sin, and that promise is extended to us today.

31:50.780 --> 31:58.232
And we have the entirety of the Scriptures that God, he is faithful to follow through and to fill his promises.

31:59.835 --> 32:07.026
And the invitation for us is to come and believe, to know that Jesus Christ is the perfect one.

32:07.426 --> 32:13.192
the son of God, the son of man who lived the perfect life, died on the cross for our sins.

32:14.173 --> 32:19.719
The very sin that tried to thwart his arrival here on earth was buried in the grave.

32:20.761 --> 32:24.885
And three days later resurrected from the grave, conquering sin, Satan, and death.

32:24.905 --> 32:29.951
And if you accept and believe that, it's not just this golden ticket that you get to heaven.

32:31.112 --> 32:36.818
It's far more beautiful than that, but it's an invitation to redeemed family.

32:37.506 --> 32:50.161
And so if that's you today, where you come from, a broken family, a broken place, where your family is messy, and you're like, man, I need other people in my life consider this invitation for you.

32:51.463 --> 33:03.698
Let me pray for us as we reflect on God's word on the beauty of a genealogy that points and validates Jesus' life.

33:04.770 --> 33:06.532
that he is in fact the Messiah.

33:06.572 --> 33:16.265
Let me pray that for us and we'll sing one more song as we close out.

33:16.285 --> 33:23.075
Lord, the gospel truly is much more than a golden ticket to heaven.

33:25.297 --> 33:31.666
I pray, I actually pray Lord that we would not render it down to something as simple as that.

33:32.514 --> 33:45.046
below the gospel, something that we can live out and experience in the here and now, through a redeemed family, redeemed people through the life, death, and resurrection of Jesus Christ.

33:45.867 --> 33:55.656
I pray that for our church family, that Riverview would be a family of messy and broken people that are just trying to figure it out, to become more like our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.

33:56.757 --> 34:02.002
I pray that we would be a family that is willing to bear one another's burdens, bear one another's mess,

34:03.362 --> 34:08.848
and that we will together come bring it to the foot of the cross and say, Lord, Lord, help us in our need.

34:10.329 --> 34:11.751
I pray that for our church, Lord.

34:12.532 --> 34:20.440
I pray that we will be known in the Lansing area, not as a church of just these people who know the theology or love the Bible or whatever.

34:20.460 --> 34:31.312
I pray that our church would be known to be a redeemed family that invites the broken, that invites the messy and says that you too, you're broken too, me too.

34:32.073 --> 34:33.234
But here is the one

34:33.442 --> 34:35.545
who saved me, who made me whole.

34:36.587 --> 34:39.332
I pray that that would be the mark of our family.

34:40.714 --> 34:48.286
Thank you for adding us to your genealogy, to your lineage, Lord, to be part of this family, Lord.

34:48.326 --> 34:50.750
It's truly a joy and a blessing.

34:51.531 --> 34:56.259
May we become more like Christ in all that we do, Lord.

34:57.081 --> 35:00.466
We thank you for your word, and we pray this in your son's name, amen.

